To overlay the metabolic fluxes, well perform differential metabolic flux analysis using Seurat.

A. Format FBA Data

First, we need to format the data, so that it matches the DGE Matrix, where rows are reactions and columns are cell IDs.

fba = mapped_flux

# Remove unnecessary columns

# Map to original IDs

fba = as.sparse(fba)

Now we need to make sure the expression matrix has the same cells as the fba matrix, and also ensure the active.ident and the Time datapoints well map to.

# Get names and indices

cell_idx = which(colnames(neut@assays$RNA@counts) %in% intersect_cells)

C. Perform data preprocessing for metabolic fluxes

Well now perform some data preprocessing steps for the metabolic fluxes. Lets define the function with the following preprocessing steps: 1. Log normalization 2. Data scaling

preprocess_flux = function(gene_obj, assay){
  # Log normalize data
  gene_obj = NormalizeData(gene_obj, 
                           assay=assay,
                           normalization.method='LogNormalize', 
                           scale.factor=10000)
  
  # Scale data
  gene_obj = ScaleData(gene_obj, 
                       assay=assay)
  return(gene_obj)
}

C. Preprocess Neutrophil Dataset

This function will find subpopulations within a given cell type. This can be used later.

find_subpopulations = function(gene_obj){
  
  # Identify variable features
  gene_obj = FindVariableFeatures(object=gene_obj, 
                              mean.function=ExpMean,
                              dispersion.function=LogVMR,
                              selection.method='vst',
                              x.low.cutoff=-Inf,
                              x.high.cutoff=Inf,
                              y.cutoff=Inf,
                              nfeatures = 2000)
  
  # Log normalize data
  gene_obj = NormalizeData(gene_obj, 
                       normalization.method='LogNormalize', 
                       scale.factor=10000)
  
  # Scale data
  all.genes = rownames(gene_obj)
  gene_obj = ScaleData(gene_obj, 
                   features=all.genes)
  
  gene_obj = SCTransform(gene_obj)

  
  # Run PCA
  gene_obj = RunPCA(object=gene_obj,
                npcs=50,
                verbose=FALSE)
  
  # Find shortest nearest neighbors and clusters
  gene_obj = FindNeighbors(gene_obj, 
                       dims=1:50,
                       reduction='pca')
  gene_obj = FindClusters(gene_obj, 
                      resolution=0.5)
  
  # Perform T-SNE
  gene_obj = RunTSNE(gene_obj,
                     dims=1:50)
  
  # Perform UMAP
  gene_obj = RunUMAP(gene_obj, 
                 dims=1:50)
  
  return(gene_obj)
}
